answers.body_markdown:
If your broker following the MQTT v3.1.1 specification detects that you have disconnected, it is entirely correct to publish the LWT. There is no way to stop this. 

@hardillb suggests that if the connection has gone down but not been noticed by the broker, then you have up to keepalive*1.5 to reconnect before the LWT is sent. This is correct. However, and this is a big however, you&#39;re relying on your loss of connection not being recognised at the broker. It might work sometimes, but it&#39;s not a condition I&#39;d want to rely on.

If this feature is very important for you, then you probably should look at using MQTT v5 instead. That will give you the option of setting the &quot;session expiry interval&quot;, which is the amount of time to keep your session active after you disconnect before sending your LWT.

